latestIgtvVideos.title: Quick NO FOUNDATION Makeup Look - Tutorial ✨
Kadha Chai/Tea Recipe to boost immunity
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Are you amongst those who don’t like the taste of kadha but do want all the goodness it contains? Don’t worry, you’re in the right place. 
This kadha chai is actually for those who cannot take normal kadha on its own. Trust me it tastes amazing & have all the goodness.

This kadha chai is a power pack of ingredients which helps in boosting the immune system. 
Undoubtedly the best drink to have at this time.

This decoction works best for protecting you against seasonal infections and keeps illness at bay. Ingredients like mulethi, cloves, ginger, black pepper, tulsi leaves and saunf are added to this drink which not just fight existing cough and cold but also increases immunity.

Ginger: Ginger has anti-viral properties and is effective against cough and cold.

Tulsi: It is a healing herb that helps in reducing mucus in the body. It also increases your immunity and fights against infections.

Black Pepper: It is anti-microbial in nature, and therefore helps to cure cold and cough.

Cloves: Packed with anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties, it soothes the throat and prevents cough.

Mulethi: Promotes digestion, anti-inflammatory and immune-boosting properties, one-shot remedy for all sorts of respiratory troubles, manages high cholesterol.

Saunf: Regulate blood pressure, reduce water retention helps purify blood, aids digestion, treats respiratory illnesses.

Few things to remember:
- Adding too much ginger can cause heartburn
- Avoid consuming Kadha during fasting as it can cause nausea
- Adding a large amount of black pepper in Kadha can lead to burning sensation in the food pipe.
